  (ZERO blank lines) imports `{ ariaSortK, sortIndicatorK }` from ./partialLogicK.rzts.
  The compiler inlines those exported arrow consts into THIS component's script BELOW
  `tickK`, before lowering; the unused `neverUsedK` export is tree-shaken.

  This is the GAP-0 LEADING seam: the spliced run's FIRST emitted token is a pure
  run-LEADING comment (`// the live sort direction …`) and the run flows ZERO blanks
  below the host `const tickK` arrow const. The inline oracle (InlineEquivHostK.rozie)
  places that comment own-line directly below `tickK` with NO blank between them.

  Before the R9 fix, the vue/svelte/solid inliner mirrors INJECT a spurious blank line
  between the host `tickK` and the spliced run's leading comment (the core
  `originalGap=0` suppression landed only in the CORE inliner, so react/angular/lit are
  byte-identical, but the vue/svelte/solid emitScript mirror paths do NOT honor the
  gap-0 leading seam and still inject the blank) → byte diff (RED on exactly
  vue/svelte/solid). This is the LEADING sibling of the R8 gap-1 TRAILING-seam fix.

  No <style> block: the scoped-CSS hash is component-name + filename derived
  (computeScopeHash), so a style block would inject a name-divergent attribute the
  byte-identity oracle (which normalizes ONLY the component name) could not reconcile
